question.Q: Do you feel pain only when eating or just after eating?
Have you had one or more teeth filled within the past week?
Does the tooth hurt only when you bite down?
See your dentist. The filling should be checked and may need to be adjusted.
See your dentist if the pain persists for more than a week. Twinges of pain are normal after having a tooth filled.
See your dentist. You may have a cavity caused by TOOTH DECAY, or you may have gingivitis (inflammation of the gums).
Do you have repeated episodes of throbbing pain in the tooth?
See your dentist. The pulp in your tooth may be inflamed because of advanced TOOTH DECAY.
Is the pain in your tooth continuous, or is your temperature 100 ℉ (37.8 ℃ ) or higher?
See a dentist immediately. You may have a TOOTH ABSCESS or severe TOOTH DECAY.
See your dentist if you are unable to make a diagnosis from this chat.
